# Styling Rules

Always follow these rules when styling components in this project.

## Tailwind CSS

### Class Merging
- **ALWAYS** use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging
- `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for proper Tailwind deduplication
- **NEVER** use template literals or string concatenation for classes
- Example:
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div className={cn("base-classes", conditional && "conditional-classes", className)} />
```

### Tailwind v4
- Project uses Tailwind CSS v4 with `@import "tailwindcss"`
- Uses CSS variables for theming (defined in `globals.css`)
- Custom variants: `@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark, .dark *))`

## Design Tokens & CSS Variables

### Color System
- **ALWAYS** use CSS variable-based colors:
  - `bg-background`, `text-foreground`
  - `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`
  - `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary-foreground`
  - `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`
  - `bg-accent`, `text-accent-foreground`
  - `bg-destructive`, `text-destructive-foreground`
  - `bg-card`, `text-card-foreground`
- **NEVER** use hardcoded colors (except for specific gradient variants)

### Border Radius
- Use `--radius` CSS variable: `rounded-lg`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-sm`
- Default: `--radius: 0.5rem`

### Spacing Scale
- Use Tailwind spacing scale: `p-4`, `gap-2`, `space-y-6`
- Common patterns:
  - Card padding: `p-6`
  - Button padding: `px-4 py-2` (default), `px-3` (sm)
  - Input padding: `px-3 py-1`
  - Gap between elements: `gap-2` (small), `gap-4` (medium), `gap-6` (large)

## Variant System

### CVA (Class Variance Authority)
- **ALWAYS** use `cva` for variant-based styling
- Define base classes first, then variants
- **ALWAYS** include `defaultVariants`
- Example:
```tsx
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "base-classes-here",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "variant-classes",
        destructive: "destructive-classes",
      },
      size: {
        default: "size-classes",
        sm: "small-size-classes",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);
```

## Custom "Vibe" Variants

### Gradient Variants
- **Primary Gradient**: `from-[#B5EAFF] to-[#00BFFF]` (blue gradient)
- **Gradient Text**: `bg-gradient-to-r from-[#B5EAFF] to-[#00BFFF] bg-clip-text text-transparent`
- **Secondary Gradient**: Uses `background-gradient1` CSS variable
- Use for interactive elements that need emphasis

### Galaxy Variant
- Border with glow: `border-2 border-input bg-transparent`
- Shadow effect: `shadow-[0_0_8px_2px_rgba(99,102,241,0.7),0_0_24px_8px_rgba(99,102,241,0.3)]`
- Hover: Enhanced shadow with `transition-all duration-300`

## Animation & Transitions

### Transition Patterns
- **Color transitions**: `transition-colors` (most common)
- **Complex animations**: `transition-all duration-300`
- **Transform optimizations**: `transform-gpu` for smooth GPU-accelerated transforms

### Hover Effects
- **Scale on hover**: `hover:scale-105` (for gradient buttons)
- **Active press**: `active:scale-[0.98]` (for button press feedback)
- **Color opacity**: `hover:bg-primary/90` (90% opacity on hover)

### Focus States
- **ALWAYS** use `focus-visible:` prefix (not `focus:`)
- **ALWAYS** include: `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2`
- Ring offset: `ring-offset-background`

### Custom Animations
- Float animation: `animate-float` (3s ease-in-out infinite)
- Wave animation: `animate-wave` (1.2s ease-in-out infinite)
- Pulse: `animate-pulse` (default), `animate-pulse-slow` (3s)
- Defined in `globals.css`

## Dark Mode

### Strategy
- Uses CSS variables with `.dark` class strategy
- Light mode: HSL colors
- Dark mode: OKLCH colors (better color consistency)
- Toggle via `.dark` class on root element

### Implementation
- **ALWAYS** use CSS variables that automatically adapt to dark mode
- **NEVER** hardcode dark mode colors - use semantic tokens
- Example:
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Uses CSS variables
<div className="bg-background text-foreground" />

// ❌ BAD - Hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-black" />
```

## Responsive Design

### Mobile-First Approach
- **ALWAYS** write mobile styles first, then add breakpoints
- Breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px), `xl:` (1280px)
- Custom breakpoint: `--breakpoint-toast-mobile: 600px`

### Font Sizes (Responsive)
- Mobile-first font sizes defined in `globals.css`
- Desktop sizes override at `md:` breakpoint
- Example: `text-base` is 13px mobile, 14px desktop

### Layout Patterns
- Flexbox: `flex items-center justify-center`
- Grid: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`
- Spacing: `space-y-4 md:space-y-6`

## Typography

### Font Sizes
- Use Tailwind text utilities: `text-xs`, `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, etc.
- Responsive sizes defined in `globals.css` (smaller on mobile)

### Font Weights
- Use semantic weights: `font-normal`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold`
- Default: `font-normal` (400)
- Headings: `font-semibold` or `font-bold`

### Line Heights
- Use Tailwind defaults or custom: `leading-none`, `leading-tight`, `leading-normal`
- Headings: `leading-none` or `leading-tight`

### Text Colors
- **ALWAYS** use semantic colors: `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary`
- Muted text: `text-muted-foreground` (for descriptions, secondary text)

## Spacing & Layout

### Padding Patterns
- Cards: `p-6` (all sides), `p-6 pt-0` (content after header)
- Buttons: `px-4 py-2` (default), `px-3` (small)
- Inputs: `px-3 py-1`
- Headers: `p-6` with `space-y-1.5` for children

### Margin Patterns
- Vertical spacing: `space-y-1.5`, `space-y-4`, `space-y-6`
- Horizontal spacing: `gap-2`, `gap-4`, `gap-6`
- Avoid margin utilities when possible - use `gap` or `space-y`

### Layout Utilities
- Container: `w-full`, `max-w-lg`, `max-w-4xl`
- Flex: `flex items-center justify-between`
- Grid: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2`

## Shadows & Borders

### Shadows
- Card: `shadow-sm` (subtle)
- Hover cards: Enhanced shadow on hover (defined in utilities)
- Custom shadows: Use arbitrary values for special effects

### Borders
- **ALWAYS** use `border` with `border-input` color
- Border radius: `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg` (uses `--radius` variable)
- Border width: `border` (1px), `border-2` (2px for special variants)

## Utilities

### Custom Utilities (from globals.css)
- `.faded-bottom`: Fade effect at bottom
- `.no-scrollbar`: Hide scrollbar
- `.card-hover`: Card hover lift effect
- `.gradient-text-blue`, `.gradient-text-green`, `.gradient-text-purple`
- `.sidebar-item-active`: Active sidebar item gradient

### Scrollbar Styling
- Custom scrollbar: 6px width/height, rounded, gradient on hover
- Defined in `globals.css` with webkit and Firefox support

## Accessibility

### Focus Styles
- **ALWAYS** use `focus-visible:` (not `focus:`)
- **ALWAYS** include: `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2`
- Ring offset: `ring-offset-background`

### Disabled States
- **ALWAYS** include: `disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50`
- Use semantic disabled styling

### Screen Reader Only
- Use `sr-only` class for visually hidden text
- Example: Icon-only buttons need `sr-only` text

## Performance

### Transform Optimizations
- Use `transform-gpu` for GPU-accelerated transforms
- Use `will-change` sparingly (only when needed)

### Animation Performance
- Prefer CSS transitions over JavaScript animations
- Use `transform` and `opacity` for smooth animations
- Avoid animating `width`, `height`, `margin`, `padding`

## Class Organization

### Order (Enforced by Biome)
- Classes are automatically sorted by Biome
- Use `useSortedClasses` rule for consistency

### Grouping
- Layout: `flex`, `grid`, `w-full`, `h-10`
- Spacing: `p-4`, `gap-2`, `space-y-4`
- Typography: `text-sm`, `font-medium`, `text-foreground`
- Effects: `shadow-sm`, `rounded-md`, `border`
- States: `hover:`, `focus-visible:`, `disabled:`
